Class Synthesis

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.epoch.synthesis.Synthesis
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ChemConstants, MechSynthConstants, FormatConstants, SynthConstants

    public class Synthesis
extends Object
implements SynthConstants
    Wraps a response synthesis, and includes methods for analyzing its validity.

      • isSelective

        public void isSelective(int kind)
                 throws SynthError
        Gets whether the chosen reactions are selective for the intermediates and products of the synthesis. Works its way backwards from the target.
        Parameters:
        kind - whether to examine the synthesis for structure-, diastereo-, or enantioselectivity
        Throws:
        SynthError - if any step in the synthesis fails to show the kind of selectivity being examined

      • oneStepIs

        public boolean oneStepIs(Synthesis authSyn,
                         int type)
                  throws SynthError
        Determines whether one step of this synthesis is a particular synthetic step. The reference sequence may contain whole molecules or substructures.
        Parameters:
        authSyn - the synthetic sequence that may be contained in this synthesis; only the last two steps are examined
        type - whether to look for entire structures or substructures
        Returns:
        false if the synthetic sequence is not found in this synthesis
        Throws:
        SynthError - if the synthetic sequence is found in this synthesis, or if the structures in a stage can't be compared to the structures in the author's stage

      • isEqualTo

        public boolean isEqualTo(Synthesis compSynth)
        Determines whether two syntheses are exactly equal by comparing the contents and reaction conditions of each stage. This definition of equality is very rigid; for example, syntheses that use similar but not identical reaction conditions will be judged different.
        Parameters:
        compSynth - the synthesis to be compared to this one
        Returns:
        true if the syntheses are exactly equal

      • isEqualTo

        Parameters:

        considerRxnConds - whether to consider reaction conditions in determining whether two syntheses are equal
        Returns:
        true if the syntheses are equal
